      "message": "[warning] Line 128: 🟡 Suggestion: The `bodyOverwrite` is applied after `init()` which already sets `body` from `msgBody`. This means `init()` may perform processing on the original body (e.g. setting type based on body content). If the overwritten body has different characteristics (e.g. different MIME type indicators), downstream logic that already ran in `init()` won\u0027t be re-evaluated. Verify that `init()` doesn\u0027t make decisions based on body content that would be invalidated by the overwrite.",
