      "side": 1,
      "message": "[warning] Line 530: 🔴 Critical: `OriginalBody` returns `item.second.commit.value(\"body\")` which gives the raw commit body. However, when `pluginData` contains a `bodyOverwrite`, the `Info::body` field is overwritten (interaction.cpp:130), but `commit[\"body\"]` still holds the original daemon body. This means editing a message will show the un-translated original text, which is correct for editing, but the role name `OriginalBody` is ambiguous — it could mean \u0027body before plugin transformation\u0027 or \u0027body before user edits\u0027. Additionally, if `commit` is empty (non-swarm messages or certain message types), this returns an empty string silently. Consider adding a fallback to `item.second.body` when `commit` doesn\u0027t contain a \"body\" key, or document that this role is only valid for swarm messages.",
